status_message:
I have always liked Bernie Sanders. I love his ideas and watching his campaign explode has been one of the best parts of this crazy election season. But when is it over? Bernie cannot win. He just can't. Hillary Clinton needs what, 88 delegates at this point to clinch? She could even have those before the June 7th primaries. If not, she will have them before the polls even close in California (she will win all she needs in New Jersey).

I hate the divisiveness that has been hurting this party. I see it all day long. I know it's hard letting go of the dream...I was originally a Hillary supporter in 2008 and when she lost it was tough. But I got excited about Obama and quickly Hillary's loss was a memory. My god, DONALD TRUMP is the Republican candidate...it is time we gather together to beat that monster...not continue this infighting over a campaign that simply cannot win. And saying that doesn't make me a shill or someone who supports war hawks...so don't go there.

I would love to hear everyone thoughts.
